  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining API Endpoints**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the API endpoints needed for `server.ts`. Right now, I\'m thinking I\'ll need an endpoint at `/api/generate-chapter`. This endpoint will call the Gemini API, taking in parameters for language, CEFR level, theme/genre, chapter number, and total chapters to generate a new story chapter.\n\n\n**Refining Google Docs Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating Google Docs. I\'m excited because client-side Firebase Auth can handle authentication using `signInWithPopup`. The user\'s Google OAuth access token empowers the client to directly call Google APIs like `docs.googleapis.com/v1/documents` using the token! This is a secure and standard pattern. The server becomes simpler.\n\n\n**Designing Server Endpoint**\n\nI\'m now writing `server.ts` and designing the `POST /api/generate-chapter` endpoint. It will handle chapter generation requests with parameters for language, CEFR level, genre, total chapters, chapter number, optional story title, previous chapters, and optional prompt notes. For chapter 1, I\'ll have the model generate and save a story title. This seems like a good route.\n\n\n**Inventing Story Titles**\n\nI\'ve realized that if a user skips providing a title, the AI can be used to generate a compelling and level-appropriate title spanning the entire story! This is fantastic, and I\'m really excited about this. It adds a powerful feature for generating stories. Now I\'m working on the Chapter 1 JSON schema. I\'m focusing on \"storyTitle\" now.\n\n\n**Defining Chapter Data Structures**\n\nI\'m now designing the JSON schema for chapter data. For subsequent chapters, the schema includes `chapterTitle`, `content`, and `vocabulary`. The vocabulary section has a structured format for words, their parts of speech, English definitions, and contextual sentences from the chapter. This structure supports level-appropriate language learning.\n\n\n**Implementing Gemini API**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the Gemini API within `server.ts` to execute the schema queries. I\'ve decided to utilize the `@google/genai` SDK and am currently determining the optimal model, leaning towards `gemini-3.5-flash` for basic text tasks like summarization and proofreading. I am eager to get this integrated into the current server and API.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/server.ts` file which sets up our full-stack server. It will initialize the Google GenAI SDK, handle the server-side proxy route for generating chapters at specific CEFR levels with custom vocab extraction, and serve the React files in production or hook into the Vite dev server inside dev mode."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 876353182
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
