  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing Initial Components**\n\nOkay, I\'ve taken a look at the foundational components. I\'m focusing on `/src/lib/auth.ts`, `/src/components/StoryConfigForm.tsx`, `/src/components/ReaderPanel.tsx`, and `/src/components/VocabularyPractice.tsx` to understand the current architecture. I think the `/src/components/ReaderPanel.tsx` component is promising.\n\n\n**Designing App Structure**\n\nI\'m now focused on fleshing out `src/App.tsx`. I\'ve outlined the core state variables needed: `activeTab`, `currentStory`, `stories`, `isLoading`, `activeChapterIndex`, `isAutoGeneratingRemaining`, `user`, `token`, `exportStatus`, and `exportedUrl`. These will manage the app\'s overall flow, including tab switching between Creation, Reading, Practice, and Library. I\'m prioritizing user experience and efficient state management.\n\n\n**Implementing New Features**\n\nI\'m now implementing dark mode, which will use a state variable, `isDarkMode`, to toggle the \'dark\' class on the document root. I\'m also adding a Google Docs export feature, which integrates Firebase Auth to provide a \"Export to Google Doc\" button with a smooth login flow. If not logged in, we prompt the Google Login. I\'m also starting to look at auto-generation of chapters.\n\n\n**Refining Chapter Generation**\n\nI\'ve just focused on chapter generation with an API call to `/api/stories/generate-chapter`, sending language, CEFR level, and other story details. The response handling now includes error checking and extraction of chapter content, title, and vocabulary. The `storyState` updates to incorporate the new chapter and check completion. I\'m aiming for robust chapter generation.\n\n\n**Optimizing Chapter Generation**\n\nI\'ve been examining the granular approach to chapter generation. I am thrilled with the sequential API calls to `/api/stories/generate-chapter`. The incremental updates and caching provide an outstanding user experience. I am particularly pleased with its resilience to potential timeouts. I am focusing on making it even more robust by implementing more error-checking on the API.\n\n\n\n**Refining Authentication Flow**\n\nI\'ve just added Google authentication and export feature and am very pleased! I\'ve confirmed that the Google authentication is triggered on export if the user isn\'t signed in, providing a seamless login flow. It caches the token. I\'ve also written an error-handling method for authentication. Finally, I\'m making sure all icons are in place.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am going to build the main frontend file `/src/App.tsx`. It acts as the core single-page engine managing full application flows: dark mode syncing, story history loading via `localStorage`, active rendering of tabs (Creation Form, Reading Desk, Practice Playground, Library Archives), account sign-in/profile status, and Google Docs API client-side execution."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 452350598
    }
  }
}
